---
/**
 * "What you can use this for" — the editorial use-case list.
 *
 * Sits directly under the luminating hero so the visitor's
 * first question after "what is this?" gets answered: "what
 * is this for?" Four short items, no cards, no icons. Type
 * does the work.
 */
import '../styles/why.css';
---
<section class="why" id="how">
  <div class="why-inner">
    <p class="why-eyebrow">What you can use this for.</p>
    <h2 class="why-lead">
      The four conversations an impact study turns into <em>investment conversations.</em>
    </h2>

    <ol class="why-list">
      <li class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__num">i.</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="why-item__name">Secure funding</h3>
          <p class="why-item__desc">Show funders, councils, and legislators exactly what your organization contributes. Impact numbers turn budget conversations into investment conversations.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__num">ii.</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="why-item__name">Compare scenarios</h3>
          <p class="why-item__desc">What happens if you cut a program, add twenty positions, expand operations, or change a policy? Model the economic consequences before you commit the resources.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__num">iii.</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="why-item__name">Streamline compliance</h3>
          <p class="why-item__desc">Federal grants, foundation reporting, and regulatory reviews keep asking for the same economic data. Generate compliance-ready outputs from the analysis you&rsquo;re already running.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li class="why-item">
        <span class="why-item__num">iv.</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="why-item__name">Tell your story</h3>
          <p class="why-item__desc">Annual reports, press releases, community presentations. Impact data makes the case in language stakeholders understand &mdash; people supported, dollars circulated.</p>
        </div>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</section>
